column4: Transfer from airport to Havelock Island by ferry boat
column9: Pick up at Port Blair Airport + Drop at jetty to board ferry + Ferry ticket charges+ Pickup at Havelock jetty + Drop to Barefoot resort {11 kms}   Please note that upon arrival at Port Blair by flight, you can proceed straight to Havelock only if your flight lands at Port Blair before 12.00hrs,  as the last ferry from Port Blair to Havelock departs at 1345hrs.

column4: Transfer from Havelock Island to Port Blair by ferry
column9: Drop back to jetty at Havelock + Ferry ticket charges + Pickup from jetty at Port Blair + Drop to chosen hotel in Port Blair (within city limits) + Pickup from hotel (within city limits) + Drop to Airport  On the return journey, from Havelock to Port Blair, you may need to stay the previous night at Port Blair if your flight departs before 14:20hrs as earlier departures are not met in time by returning ferry from Havelock.
column22: Havelock to Port Blair htl + htl to a/p

Jeep safari in Sasangir National Park
column9: Safaris in Gir National Park are supposed to be booked 3 months prior to required safari dates. We have taken the highest safari rate, applicable for Festival Dates (Navratri/Diwali/Christmas & New Year) per safari for foreigners.  The park is open from 16 October to 15 June. Best time to visit is definitely late November to early March, when the temperature can drop to a cool 10°C. The summer months are scorching hot, with the temperature hitting 43°C.

column4: Jeep safari in Velavadar National Park
column9: Entrance fees for a jeep are actually lower on weekdays than on weekends. We have taken the higher amount for our costing.  The park is open throughout the year but mid-June to March is best time to visit.   For bird watchers winter months of December to March are the best time to visit when many migratory birds arrive to spend the winters here.

column9: The canter safari to Dhikala only operates from 15 Nov to 15 May                There are 2 safaris that can be taken in a day -       Morning safari - from 6 to 10 AM.       Afternoon safari - from 2 to 6 PM.              There is a limit in the no of jeeps that can enter the forest in a day.       Therefore we advice you to book the Jungle safari in 4x4 open Gypsies in advance.
